[2] Guinea: UNMEER logistics center back in operation following warehouse fire
Date: Wed 24 Dec 2014
Source: UN News Centre [edited]
http://www.un.org/apps/news/story.asp?NewsID=49688


The UN Mission for Ebola Emergency Response (UNMEER) has reported that a main United Nations logistics hub managed by the World Food Programme (WFP) in Guinea is fully operational despite the fire that swept through the facility last week threatening medicines and laboratory materials used in the fight against Ebola. The facility is located in the main humanitarian logistics base of the airport and of the city of Conakry, the capital of Guinea. UNMEER stated "The cold chain capacity has already been re-established via the setup of donated refrigerated 40 foot containers."...

According to the latest update released today [24 Dec 2014] by WHO, 19 497 people have now been affected by Ebola, with 7588 reported deaths, including 666 health care workers who are known to have been infected up to the end of 21 Dec [2014], 366 of whom have died [but see updated figures in [1] above. - Mod.JW]

