******
[4] Sierra Leone: no new cases in Pujehun District
Date: 24 Dec 2014
Source: Awareness Times [edited]
http://news.sl/drwebsite/publish/article_200526934.shtml


The district medical officer for Pujehun District, Dr David Bome has told the Awareness Times that they have gone for over 3 weeks without any Ebola case. Via telephone interview on 23 Dec 2014, Dr Bome disclosed that Pujehun is on top of the current Ebola situation owning to the participatory role play by all stakeholders including youths, women, the district health medical team and the Pujehun District Descendants Association as well as government efforts. He disclosed that the last Ebola case surfaced in the district on 26 Nov [2014]...

[byline: Augustine Samba]

--
communicated by:
