[8] Region: Chinese military to test Ebola vaccine
Date: Fri 26 Dec 2014
Source: Economic Times [edited]
http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/world-news/chinese-military-to-test-ebola-vaccine-this-month/articleshow/45644727.cms


The Chinese military has developed and will test an Ebola vaccine on humans in December 2014, a defense ministry spokesman said Thu 24 Dec 2014. Spokesman Yang Yujun said at a regular press briefing that the vaccine has been developed by a research team at the Academy of Military Medical Sciences. "The vaccine has recently passed appraisal by state and military authorities," Xinhua quoted Yang as saying.

Yang said the China-developed Ebola vaccine was the 3rd one to have been put into clinical tests in the world. It is also the 1st 1st genetic mutation Ebola vaccine in the world.

