[10] Guinea-Bissau: no news good news?
Date: 14 Dec 2014 [no update since then]
Source: Crofsblogs [edited]
http://crofsblogs.typepad.com/h5n1/2014/12/waiting-for-ebola-news-from-guinea-bissau.html


Sundays are slow news days at best, but the absence of reports from Guinea-Bissau is slightly maddening. I know it's a small country, a former Portuguese colony, but surely someone in Bissau or a neighbouring country must know what's happening with the suspected Ebola case who crossed the border from Guinea-Conakry.

Aggravating the problem is that Guinea-Bissau seems to have just a couple of online news sources, one of which is weeks out of date. Neither has a word about Ebola; the original report on the suspected case came from a francophone source, which hasn't updated the story since Fri [12 Dec 2014]. And the government has no health ministry that I can find.

